                <td height="622" valign="top" colspan="2" bgcolor="#004142">&nbsp;<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4"><tr bgcolor="#000000"><td><font color="#FFFFFF"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial" size="6">Why Hidden Base fears not the Gand</font></td></tr></table><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td></td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Rating</Font></TD><TD><IMG SRC="images/a4.gif" BORDER=0><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=476"><IMG SRC="images/aread.GIF" BORDER=0></A><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=476"><IMG SRC="images/areview.GIF" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="../membercenter/directory/memberpage.php3?member=1805">Kenneth "Ken Bradford" Bradford</A></FONT></TD></TR><!-- 1805 --><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Description</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This article details how Hidden Base most certainly is not dead--and why the X-Swarm player need not fear a Gand named Zuckuss....</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Article</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Hidden Base Need Not Fear the Gand<br>
----------------------------------<br>
<br>
There has been some grumbling amongst some local players that Zuckuss is too powerful, and how Light Side space is dead.  It leaves the Light Side player pining for the days of pre-errata Hidden Base....well, maybe not that far, but it is a common belief that the Light Side has no business in space right now.	I bought into it too after realizing what Dengar in Punishing One, Ig-88 in IG-2000, and Zuckuss in Mist Hunter would do to my poor X-Swarm of 5 X-Wings draining peacefully at Kessel.<br>
<br>
Of course, whenever a deck is believed to be dead, it's usually the best time to adapt it and play it.  And although room is tight in every deck, a refocusing of the Hidden Base deck would aid in the fight against the Bounty Hunter Space Brigade.<br>
<br>
Because Dark Side did not venture into space much following S-Foils + Organized Attack, the Hidden Base player usually found himself with slots to spare.  Some players (myself included) usually went the Proj of Skywalker/TK422/ICBW route, usually to such a great extent that the DS was powerless to damage you on the ground.  Those days are unlikely to return, and while it would be prudent to keep some drain protection (or an EPP hit squad or two), it is now necessary to fill those slots with great cards which ensure dominance in space.<br>
<br>
A nifty little card entitled 'X-Wing Laser Cannons' leads the assault.  A great card with a destiny 5, it went unused for a while because, quite simply, there was nothing for the Light Side player to shoot at.  Now, with the influx of the awesome ECC and EJP Bounty Hunter/ship combos, and a renewed confidence of the DS of their ability to battle in space, the LS player is guaranteed a few targets to peck at.<br>
The great part is that you can either fire for free for straight destiny in a pinch, or you can spend up to 3 force to add that much to your shot.  The best part?  When you use 3 force, and hit the target, they're immediately lost!<br>
Zuckuss won't be there to work his magic!  Dengar will be 'Lost in Space', so to speak!  This is simply awesome, and a great way to counter these pesky foes.<br>
<br>
For those worried about the more maneuverable ships, such as Fett in Slave 1 (with a nimble maneuver of 6, including Fett's bonus) there is another card which will aid even more.  Steady Aim is a Blaster Proficiency in space, adding 2 as a used or 4 as a lost to your shot.  Chuck this baby to the lost pile, spend three force, and try to miss any starfighter in the game with a *+7* modifier to your draw.  Yikes!<br>
<br>
The last card which is the icing on the cake is Stay Sharp!<br>
Everyone is familiar with Sorry About The Mess/Sniper, but many times I have played this card to hear, 'what does that do?'. They are usually not happy to find out.	It is quite nasty to eliminate Zuckuss before the battle begins, and it's a destiny 4 *used* interrupt.  Even nastier is when they have Bossk in Bus and Dengar in Punishing 1 blocking your drain, counting on two destiny...and when the smoke clears, Dengar is alone, nifty gametext still active, but no destiny...*sniff* breaks my heart, and I'm sure it will yours too next time you pull off this trick on the newfound Darkside fleet.<br>
<br>
And without those guys...remember the heydey of Power 6, free deploy, immune to attrition X-Wings?  They can be yours again, for the mere price of a few  card lots.Gun 'em down, and force choke 'n drain away.  Happy days are here again!<br>
<br>
<br>
Ken Bradford<br>
<br>
BradfordKen@hotmail.com<br>
<br>
<br>
